Read only Stores:
- allow to create const variables, that will error when code change them outside the initial creation of their content
- create a runtime lock in stores to make them readonly, this will panic under development and silently ignore the changes in production builds
- allow to inspect and set this lock from loft code with d#lock = true and reading the boolean
- do not allow the lock to be set via an expression other than the constant boolean
- setting a const variable or argument to d#lock = false is illegal
- requestion a d#lock on a const structure will aways return true
- only during development builds will the const variables and arguments be automatically set to true, in production they will be locked only with the explicit setting from the code
- create tests on this functionality
- document this functionality

Allow multi-threading:
- make a pool of threads that can perform compilations, define the number of possible threads on creation.
- allow a function to be performed by multiple threads with data read from a table with data for the input for each thread.
- the data from this and potential other databases given to this function is forced read only.
- each function can create thread local data and return it to the main task to further process.
- during the threading phase with with threading the data structures that are given to the function are read only, create a read-only flag inside the store.
- validate this in unit-tests.

